#: ../preferences.rst:66
msgid "Themes"
msgstr ""

#: ../preferences.rst:67
msgid "OpenShot comes with 3 standard themes, which change the look and feel of the program."
msgstr ""

#: ../preferences.rst:69
msgid "**Cosmic Dusk:** [Default Theme] A bluish theme with a more modern UI design, enhancing the visual aesthetics of the editor. This theme features shades of blue and purple, giving the interface a contemporary and dynamic feel. It combines modern aesthetics with functionality, offering a fresh and visually appealing workspace for video editing."
msgstr ""

#: ../preferences.rst:70
msgid "**Humanity Dark:** A dark theme with dark gray tones, providing a modern and sleek look. This theme is designed for users who prefer working in low-light conditions or who enjoy a more subdued and professional appearance. The dark gray background reduces glare and eye strain, making it suitable for extended editing sessions."
msgstr ""

#: ../preferences.rst:71
msgid "**Retro:** A light theme that offers a classic and clean appearance. This theme uses light gray and white tones, making it ideal for users who prefer a bright and high-contrast interface. It provides a traditional look that is easy on the eyes, especially in well-lit environments."
msgstr ""

#: ../preferences.rst:76
msgid "Restoring Defaults"
msgstr ""

#: ../preferences.rst:77
msgid "In OpenShot, each preferences category (or tab) in the Preferences window has a **Restore Defaults** button that allows you to easily reset the values for that specific category. This feature is particularly useful if you want to reset only certain parts of your preferences, like keyboard shortcuts, without affecting the rest of your custom settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../preferences.rst:81
msgid "**Where to Find the Restore Defaults Button:** Each category or tab in the Preferences window has a **Restore Defaults** button located in the bottom left corner of the screen. The name of the button updates based on the category you’re viewing. For example, if you're in the \"Keyboard\" tab, the button will say **Restore Defaults: Keyboard**."
msgstr ""

#: ../preferences.rst:86
msgid "**How It Works:** Only the settings in the currently selected category will be restored to their default values. This selective restoration makes it easy to reset certain preferences without affecting others."
msgstr ""

#: ../preferences.rst:90
msgid "**Tip for Beginners:** - If you're not sure about a change you've made in a particular category, don’t hesitate to use the **Restore Defaults** button. It’s a simple way to undo changes and get back to the default settings for that specific category without affecting your overall setup."
msgstr ""

